People like to use MML because it is a well established standart, in use for like 30 years, and there are many compilers around. I don't think a new music language will get a real use, because there aren't too many MML users around these days.<br /><br />Speaking of making graphics on paper sheets, I did that too, in mid 90s. It is kind of fun, just not very productive.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Mon Jul 22, 2013 10:54 am</p><hr />
